  "text": "We employed several computational approaches to systematically identify self-interacting regions in CEF genome ( Figure 3 ; Table 1 ). The original algorithm proposed by Dixon et al. [CITATION_1] reported ∼1250 large domains with a median size 640 kb (average size ∼770 kb). The Armatus algorithm (59) revealed ∼3100 smaller domains with a median size 240 kb (average size ∼310 kb). Finally, the TADtree algorithm, which finds hierarchical sets of domains representing TADs and subTADs, produced nested sets of regions with average and median length varying between 160 and 260 kb (Table 1) .",
