    "4301920": {
      "title": "Topological domains in mammalian genomes identified by analysis of chromatin interactions",
      "abstract": "The three-dimensional organization of the human and mouse genomes in embryonic stem cells and terminally differentiated cell types is investigated, revealing that large, megabase-sized chromatin interaction domains are a pervasive and conserved structural feature of genome organization."
